  "local_port": 47406,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do I eat on the Ketogenics Diet?",
  "response": "The ketogenic diet is a high-fat, low-carbohydrate diet designed to induce ketosis, a metabolic state where your body burns fat for fuel instead of carbohydrates. Here are some key food categories and examples of what you can eat on a ketogenic diet:\n\n### 1. Healthy Fats\n- **Oils**: Olive oil, coconut oil, avocado oil.\n- **Butter and Ghee**: Grass-fed if possible.\n- **Avocados**: Fresh or in the form of guacamole.\n- **Nuts and Seeds**: Almonds, walnuts, chia seeds, flaxseeds (in moderation).\n\n### 2. Protein Sources\n- **Meat**: Beef, pork, lamb, and poultry (preferably grass-fed or organic).\n- **Fish**: Salmon, sardines, mackerel, and other fatty fish.\n- **Eggs**: Free-range or organic eggs are preferred.\n- **Dairy**: Cheese, heavy cream, and full-fat yogurt (limited amounts).\n\n### 3. Low-Carbohydrate Vegetables\n- **Leafy Greens**: Spinach, kale, Swiss chard, and lettuce.\n- **Cruciferous Vegetables**: Broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts.\n- **Other Veggies**: Zucchini, bell peppers, asparagus, mushrooms.\n\n### 4. Berries (in moderation)\n- **Berries**: Strawberries, blueberries, raspberries, and blackberries.\n\n### 5. Beverages\n- **Water**: Always a primary choice.\n- **Tea and Coffee**: Unsweetened, with optional added fats like coconut oil or heavy cream.\n- **Bone Broth**: Rich in nutrients and good for maintaining electrolyte balance.\n\n### 6. Other Foods\n- **Condiments**: Mustard, mayonnaise (sugar-free), and low-carb dressings.\n- **Sweeteners**: Stevia, erythritol, and monk fruit (used sparingly).\n\n### Foods to Avoid\n- **Grains**: Wheat, rice, pasta, and bread.\n- **Sugars**: Soda, candy, and other sugary snacks.\n- **High-Carb Fruits**: Bananas, apples, and oranges.\n- **Starchy Vegetables**: Potatoes, sweet potatoes, and corn.\n- **Legumes**: Beans, lentils, and chickpeas.\n\n### Tips for Success\n- **Plan Meals**: Prepare meals ahead of time to avoid high-carb temptations.\n- **Check Labels**: Be mindful of hidden sugars and carbs in packaged foods.\n- **Stay Hydrated**: Drink plenty of water and manage electrolytes to avoid keto flu.\n\nAlways consult with a healthcare provider before starting any new diet plan, especially if you have underlying health conditions.",
